#
# Every image build (apps/server/Dockerfile, apps/web/Dockerfile) uses the
# repository root as its build context (see documentation/dev/containers.md),
# so this file keeps that context small and keeps host-local artifacts —
# especially node_modules built for the host's own OS/arch, which would
# silently break better-sqlite3's native binding inside the Linux
# containers — out of the image entirely.

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image; host node_modules may be built
# for a different OS/arch than the container, notably better-sqlite3's
# native binding on a macOS host)
**/node_modules

# Build output (rebuilt inside the image)
**/dist
**/build
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Generated route tree (regenerated by the Vite build)
apps/web/src/routeTree.gen.ts

# Test / coverage
**/coverage
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx

# Generated data (SQLite, recordings) — never belongs in an image layer
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite-shm
**/*.sqlite-wal
data/
recordings/

# Editor / OS
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode

# Version control and CI
.git
.github

# Docs are not needed inside any image
documentation/
README.md
LICENSE
NOTICE
